gomodel:SYNGO_2877  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Dynamin-3 Concentrates in Dendritic Spines and Correlates with the Presence of an Endocytic Zone\"\nFig.3: \"Dynamin-3 Localizes to Spine Membrane Domains Lateral to the PSD\". Experimental description: - \"Hippocampal neuron cultures were prepared from E18 rat embryos ...\"\n- Overexpressed Dynamin-3; DNM3 is of rat species: \"PSD-95-GFP was provided by David\nBredt. EGFP tagged dynamin-1aa (Homo sapiens), dynamin-2ab (Rattus norvegicus) and\ndynamin-3aaa (Rattus norvegicus) were gifts from Mark McNiven\"" ;
